Date: Mon, 25 Mar 2024 21:15:10 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 11/15] net: emaclite: Fix xemaclite_aligned_read() of trailing
 bytes

The final loop in xemaclite_aligned_read() to copy upto three
trailing bytes was missing the increment of the pointers.

Signed-off-by: Stuart Menefy <stuart.menefy@codasip.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/xilinx/xilinx_emaclite.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/xilinx/xilinx_emaclite.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/xilinx/xilinx_emaclite.c
index 22812cb33738..272062e72da6 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/xilinx/xilinx_emaclite.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/xilinx/xilinx_emaclite.c
@@ -273,7 +273,7 @@ static void xemaclite_aligned_read(const void __iomem *reg, u8 *dest_ptr,
 
 		/* Read the remaining data */
 		for (; length > 0; length--)
-			*to_u8_ptr = *from_u8_ptr;
+			*to_u8_ptr++ = *from_u8_ptr++;
 	}
 }
 
